description:
Imam Zaid Shakir at Muhammad Ali’s memorial service on Friday. (AP Photo/David Goldman)

Following Bill Clinton’s eulogy at Muhammad Ali’s memorial service in Louisville on Friday, Imam Zaid Shakir askedÂ those in attendance to rise, observe a moment of silence and reflect on what the champ meant to them as the Ali family exited the KFC Yum! Center.

Shakir then recited two poems he wrote about AliÂ and offered a closing prayer.

“His body is down, but his spirit is up,” Shakir said, “and it will stay up as long as we keep it up.”
